			},
			"created_at": "2026-03-16T13:05:53Z",
			"updated_at": "2026-03-16T13:06:34Z",
			"body": "This code change does seem to mitigate the issue, however because of the 600ms debounce, if you change the search term and then scroll immediately after the content updates, it will scroll to the top of the log a second time, which is kind of annoying.\r\n\r\nSee video:\r\nhttps://github.com/user-attachments/assets/2a58a200-aea5-415b-80e8-676c72b913eb",
			"author_association": "COLLABORATOR",
