		{
			"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/laurent22/joplin/issues/comments/4069533798",
			"html_url": "https://github.com/laurent22/joplin/pull/14757#issuecomment-4069533798",
			"issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/laurent22/joplin/issues/14757",
			"id": 4069533798,
			"node_id": "IC_kwDOBLftOs7ykChm",
			"user": {
				"login": "KareemAlaa1",
				"id": 96543783,
				"node_id": "U_kgDOBcEkJw",
				"avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/96543783?v=4",
				"gravatar_id": "",
				"url": "https://api.github.com/users/KareemAlaa1",
				"html_url": "https://github.com/KareemAlaa1",
				"followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/KareemAlaa1/followers",
				"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/KareemAlaa1/following{/other_user}",
				"gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/KareemAlaa1/gists{/gist_id}",
				"starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/KareemAlaa1/starred{/owner}{/repo}",
				"subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/KareemAlaa1/subscriptions",
				"organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/KareemAlaa1/orgs",
				"repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/KareemAlaa1/repos",
				"events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/KareemAlaa1/events{/privacy}",
				"received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/KareemAlaa1/received_events",
				"type": "User",
				"user_view_type": "public",
				"site_admin": false
			},
			"created_at": "2026-03-16T17:51:24Z",
			"updated_at": "2026-03-16T17:52:22Z",
			"body": "> This code change does seem to mitigate the issue, however because of the 600ms debounce, if you change the search term and then scroll immediately after the content updates, it will scroll to the top of the log a second time, which is kind of annoying.\r\n> \r\n> See video: https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/2a58a200-aea5-415b-80e8-676c72b913eb\r\n\r\nThanks for feedback.\r\n\r\nI see two possible directions here:\r\n\r\n1. We can cancel the debounce and refresh immediately on each filter change. That should remove the delayed second jump, but it may be significantly heavier on large logs because filtering would run on every keystroke.\r\n \r\n2. We can keep the debounce and current search behavior. In practice, filtered results are usually different from the items currently visible, so some repositioning is expected when we replace old data with new filtered data. Starting from the top is also reasonable for search, since it shows the first matching results first.\r\n\r\nAlso, there was a redundant [scrollToOffset](vscode-file://vscode-app/usr/share/code/resources/app/out/vs/code/electron-browser/workbench/workbench.html) causing an extra jump, so I removed that duplicate call to reduce the annoyance.\r\n\r\nIf you have other suggestions, I’d be happy to try them.",
			"author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
			"reactions": {
				"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/laurent22/joplin/issues/comments/4069533798/reactions",
				"total_count": 0,
				"+1": 0,
				"-1": 0,
				"laugh": 0,
				"hooray": 0,
				"confused": 0,
				"heart": 0,
				"rocket": 0,
				"eyes": 0
			},
			"performed_via_github_app": null
		},
