				"events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mrjo118/events{/privacy}",
				"received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mrjo118/received_events",
				"type": "User",
				"user_view_type": "public",
				"site_admin": false
			},
			"created_at": "2026-03-16T18:34:56Z",
			"updated_at": "2026-03-16T18:34:56Z",
			"body": "I think we should still keep the debounce, as logs can get very long. I wasn't complaining about moving to the top every time you change the filter, I think that is an acceptable caveat. The issue was the additional call to scrollToOffset, which you have now addressed. From my perspective now, it looks good to me",
